    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 1518/191.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial Chinese Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that by an
                    imperial edict published on the 28th instant, it has been decided to designate,
                    beginning with the first noon of next year, the title of reign of His Imperial
                    Majesty, the new Emperor of China as Hsiiant’ung, and by the same edict the 9th
                    day of the present moon (Dec. 2) has been appointed as the auspicious day on
                    which His Majesty will formally ascend the Imperial Throne. Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wu Ting Fang.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
